asil|CRB]]\n| manageryears7 = 2003\u20132004\n| managerclubs7 = [[Centro Sportivo Alagoano|CSA]]\n| manageryears8 = 2004\n| managerclubs8 = [[America Football Club (Rio de Janeiro)|America (RJ)]]\n| manageryears9 = 2004\u20132005\n| managerclubs9 = [[Rio Branco Atl\u00e9tico Clube|Rio Branco (ES)]]\n| manageryears10 = 2005\u20132008\n| managerclubs10 = [[Stade Tunisien]]\n| manageryears11 = 2008\u20132009\n| managerclubs11 = [[Kazma Sporting Club|Kazma]]\n| manageryears12 = 2009\n| managerclubs12 = [[Al-Shamal Sports Club|Al-Shamal]]\n| manageryears13 = 2009\u20132010\n| managerclubs13 = [[ES Hammam-Sousse|Hammam-Sousse]]\n| manageryears14 = 2010\u20132011\n| managerclubs14 = [[Legi\u00e3o Futebol Clube|Legi\u00e3o]]\n| manageryears15 = 2012\u20132013\n| managerclubs15 = [[Stade Gab\u00e8sien]]\n| manageryears16 = 2013\u20132014\n| managerclubs16 = [[Grombalia Sports]]\n| manageryears17 = 2014\u20132016\n| managerclubs17 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Sport Avia\u00e7\u00e3o|ASA]]\n| manageryears18 = 2018\u20132019\n| managerclubs18 = [[Rayon Sports F.C.|Rayon Nyanza]]\n}}\n\n'''Roberto Oliveira Gon\u00e7alves do Carmo''' (born 22 June 1960), known as '''Robertinho''', is a Brazilian [[Association football|football]] manager and former player. As a player, Robertinho played at both professional and international levels as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Rio de Janeiro]], Robertinho played club football in Brazil, Portugal and Switzerland for [[Fluminense Football Club|Fluminense]], [[Clube de Regatas do Flamengo|Flamengo]], [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]], [[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]], [[Sport Club do Recife|Sport Recife]], [[Clube Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro|Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro]], [[C.D. Nacional|Nacional]] and Gr\u00f6ssembacher.<ref name=\"nft\">{{NFT player|id=30771|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foradejogo.net/player.php?player=196006220001|title=Profile|language=Portuguese|publisher=Fora de Jogo}}</ref>\n\nHe earned one international cap for [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] on 25 September 1980, against Paraguay.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sambafoot.com/en/trainers/516_robertinho.html|title=Profile|publisher=Sambafoot}}</ref>\n\nRobertinho became manager of Tunisian club [[Stade Tunisien]] for the second time in September 2007; he had previously coached Brazilian clubs [[Americano Futebol Clube|Americano]] and [[Fluminense Football Club|Fluminense]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/africa/7016474.stm|title=Robertinho to coach Stade Tunisien|date=27 September 2007|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{FootballDatabase.eu|95796<!-- --robertinho -->}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Robertinho managerial positions\n|list1=\n{{Brasil de Pelotas managers}}\n{{Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento managers}}\n{{Fluminense Football Club managers}}\n{{Centro Sportivo Alagoano managers}}\n{{Clube de Regatas Brasil managers}}\n{{America Football Club managers}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Robertinho}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Rio de Janeiro (city)]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Brazilian footballers]]\n[[Category:Brazilian football managers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Angola]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Rwanda]]\n[[Category:Brazil international footballers]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A managers]]\n[[Category:Fluminense FC players]]\n[[Category:Clube de Regatas do Flamengo footballers]]\n[[Category:Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras players]]\n[[Category:Sport Club Internacional players]]\n[[Category:Sport Club do Recife players]]\n[[Category:Botafogo de Futebol e Regatas players]]\n[[Category:C